37 chapter one hundred and fifty-one B arising out of or in the course of his occupation as a licensed
38 broker or salesman, shall suspend forthwith the license of said broker or salesman for a period of
39 sixty days, provided, however that if the board determines that the violation by such licensed
40 broker or salesman occurred within two years of the date of a prior finding by a court or agency
41 of a violation of chapter one hundred and fifty-one B, which prior finding has become final, it
42 shall forthwith suspend the license of such broker or salesman for a period of one hundred and
43 eighty days. The board shall suspend the license of a broker or salesman for any violation of
44 chapter one hundred and fifty-one B referred to it under this section. Commissions and agencies
45 empowered to make referrals to the board under this section shall make all referrals that qualify
46 under this section and shall not have discretion as to whether to make the referral.
47 SECTION 4. Section 87SS of said chapter 112 of the General Laws, as so appearing, is
48 hereby amended by striking out the second sentence and inserting in place thereof the following
49 sentence:-
50 Every individual applicant for a license as a salesman who is required to take an
51 examination therefore shall, as a prerequisite to taking such examination, submit proof
52 satisfactory to the board that he has completed courses in real estate subjects approved by the
53 board, such courses to total 40 classroom hours of instruction and must include at least 4 hours
54 on fair housing law or diversity and inclusion in real estate; provided, however, that applicants
55 having successfully completed a course in real property while enrolled in an accredited law
56 school in the commonwealth may also take such examination.
3 of 4

57 SECTION 5. Section 87XX 1/2 of said chapter 112 of the General Laws, as so appearing,
58 is hereby amended by striking out the first paragraph and inserting in place thereof the following
59 paragraph:-
60 Section 87XX1/2. Any person holding a license as a real estate broker or salesman shall,
61 within their renewal period, satisfactorily complete courses or programs of instruction approved
62 by the board; provided that attendance at such courses or programs of instruction shall be no less
63 than six hours but no more than twelve hours as determined by the board. The curriculum
64 contained in such courses or programs shall contain at least six hours of instruction concerning
65 or related to compliance with laws and regulations, including at least two hours on fair housing
66 or diversity and inclusion in real estate, and four hours selected from any of the following
67 subjects: equal employment opportunity; accessibility for the disabled; agency law;
68 environmental issues in real estate; zoning and building codes; real estate appraisal and
69 financing; property tax assessments and valuation; and real estate board regulations. The board
70 shall certify in advance the curriculum forming the basis of such courses or programs which
71 satisfy the provisions of this section.
